  "text": "Sandrelli and Jerez [CITATION_1] describe the evolution of authoring programs for interpreters, starting with Interpr-IT, through Interpretations, and finally to Black Box 3.0. They highlighting functionalities such as a voice recording feature, on-screen note-pad, pitch-tracker for gauging performance etc. While authoring options go beyond the IVY environment, some similar tools may be integrated in the future.",
